import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["size"].median():.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    avg_size = data.groupby('name')['size'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_size['name'], avg_size['size'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Name')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Size')
    ax.set_title('What is the average size of the items in the dataset?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['parent'] = data['parent'].astype(str)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['parent'] == parent]['size'] for parent in data['parent'].unique()], labels=data['parent'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Parent')
    ax.set_ylabel('Size')
    plt.title('What is the size distribution of items by their parent?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['name', 'size']]
    data = data.groupby('name')['size'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    plt.title('What is the size distribution of items by their name?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Density')
    for name in data['name'].unique():
        subset = data[data['name'] == name]
        plt.plot(subset['size'], subset.index, label=name)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()

    plt.title('What is the relationship between size and id?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
